Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Landschaften, Photos"

- Reproductions of landscape paintings by different artists
- Empty folder addressed to "Herrn Dr. G. H. Evers Heidelberg Bismarchstr. 17" and dated 18.01.1943
    
Loose documentation reunited with the folder:   
    
- Photograph of a painting of a landscape with two shepherds (one playing flute) and sheep.  
- [in all probability originally part of Akte 24:] Two photographs (one complete and one detail) of a painting of a landscape with a water mill at the centre.  
  
Loose documentation in the Rubensdocumentation of the Rubenianum:   
     
- Photo of 'The Consequences of War'
- Photo of the 'Offer till Venus'
